This paper is about training Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) for image synthesis, which is a popular topic in computer vision (CV) research. Therefore, cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a new regularization technique for GANs, which falls under the category of machine learning (LG) and artificial intelligence (AI). Additionally, the paper involves manipulating the input or feature space of the discriminator, which could be considered as a graphics (GR) or neural networks (NE) topic.
